Defendant in custody.
The State files an Amended Information amending count 1 to 3rd degree sexual assault contrary to Section 940.225(3) a Class G felony.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge of 3rd degree sexual assault.  Convictged.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, expose child to harmful material.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
3) Obtain high school diploma or equivalent;
4) Maintain absolute sobriety;
5) No contact with the victim, N.J.G., DOB: 08-12-2002;
6) Pay court costs of $518.00 and supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) Provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
8) Undergo any sex offender treatment as required;
9) Comply with the Sex Offender Registry.
Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.
